post_summaries.description: The image is a post on Instagram by terencetbooker. It features a picture of the cover of a book titled "The Book of North American Tribes, Chiefs, Warriors & Their Stories." The cover has a collage of portraits of Native American people. The post's caption discusses the historical context of how some Native American groups were classified.

The Instagram post shows a family tree exploration, specifically focusing on Marie Catherine Wiame, the wife of the poster's 8th great-grandfather. The post also includes a caption encouraging others to explore their ancestry and know their roots, along with relevant hashtags.

The image is a screenshot of an Instagram post by terencetbooker. The post shows a family tree/genealogy chart of William E. White, his 4th great-grandfather. The post also includes a lengthy caption discussing the historical shift in racial classifications, specifically from "mulatto" to "black," and the impact of laws like the Racial Integrity Act.
The image shows terencetbooker posing with another man. The caption includes "#throwbackthursday #bobmarley".

The image is an Instagram post by terencetbooker about "Ethnic Relations and Migration in the Ancient World," specifically focusing on Herodotus's writings on Ethiopians. The post includes hashtags related to Black history, knowledge, excellence, and ancient civilizations.

The image is a screenshot of an Instagram post by terencetbooker. The post features a block of text discussing the history of Cape Verde and its connection to Portuguese colonial expansion and the slave trade. The post also includes hashtags related to Black history, Moors, African diaspora, and self-knowledge.
